The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Sumita Chatterjee, a 30-year-old homemaker, and Indranath Ghosh, 38, died after they allegedly jumped in front of a train at Ichhapore railway station late on Tuesday. Police suspect the two were having an affair. Police said Sumita, who lived in Madhyamgram, had gone to her parents house in Ichhapore on Tuesday. Commuters at the station saw Sumita and Indranath, who also lived in Ichhapore, jump in front of a Sealdah-bound train around 11pm.																																																		   In another incident, trader Shankar Sarkar, 22, allegedly jumped in front of a goods train between Dum Dum and Belghoria stations on Wednesday morning.     Two persons died in separate road accidents on Wednesday morning. Kalipada Ghosh, 27, died after a minibus hit the lorry he was driving on Jujarsaha-Munshirhat Road in Howrah. Police said local residents took Kalipada to a health centre, where he was declared dead. The minibus was impounded but the driver fled. In the other mishap, a 50-year-old man was hit by an unidentified vehicle at the Gariahat crossing. He was taken to AMRI Hospitals in Dhakuria, where he was declared dead.    Damayanti Sen became the first woman detective chief of the city on Wednesday. Sen, who was deputy commissioner (central), succeeded Jawed Shamim, now joint commissioner (headquarters).    A Calcutta-Silchar Air India flight carrying 138 passengers returned to the city at 3pm on Wednesday within 20 minutes of take-off because of a snag in the engine. The flight will leave on Thursday afternoon.    The decomposed body of Nehasish Mitra, 45, was found at his Dr Kartik Bose Street house in north Calcutta on Wednesday morning. Police said Mitra lived alone and had been suffering from a chronic illness.    A.K. Garg has joined the Calcutta Telephones as chief general manager.                                                                                                                                                                   
